HEADWORD: Pontific
<hw>Pon*tif"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>pontificius</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to, or
consisting of, pontiffs or priests.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>pontific</xex>
college with their augurs and flamens.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the pope; papal.</def>
<rj><au>Shenstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pontifical</ent>⟦br⟧
